## What is Rabbel

Rabbel (rabbel.se) is a Swedish word game, where the objective is to work out the various possible words from a given NxN square of alphabets. Words can be formed by linking together alphabets in any order, as long as they are:

- adjacent to the preceeding character.
- the formed word doesn't have any closed loops, i.e. traversing of an alphabet more than once.

Rabbel uses the dictionaries from the Swedish Academy, available on svenska.se

## Purpose of rabbelrouser

As a immigrant to Sweden who has learned Swedish later in life, I'm constantly looking at ways to improve my Swedish vocabulary, and Rabbel appealed to me, but after I'd solved the words that I knew about, the game would then devolve into randomly sweeping together words, and hoping to get lucky, in order to learn a new word, or unlock a word-reveal. rabbelrouser is an attempt to get a helping hand, and to make it easier to learn new words.


## rabbelrouser: how it works

-rabbelrouser is a program that that accepts an NxN matrix of characters as input, and an optional list of contraints, and proceeds to generate an exhaustive list of possible words, that can then be fed to a dictionary lookup program, to list out the valid words.
- rabbelrouser is only the generator or permutator tool; the dictionary lookups is made using a tool called sv-eng.

## Setting up

rabbelrouser's git repository uses the sv-eng program as a git submodule. Either clone rabbelrouser recursively, to directly fetch the submodule, or execute the setupsub.sh script, which apart from fetching the submodule, sets up the sv-eng program for use.

```bash
git clone https://github.com/pchengi/rabbelrouser.git
cd rabbelrouser
bash setupsub.sh
```

## Input file

The input for the rabbelrouser program, is a text file, with multiple rows of comma-separated characters.
Here's a sample input file, below.

```
E,A,E,E
Å,R,E,N
A,S,E,I
T,U,N,S
```

## Constraints file

Constraints can be specified in a text file, with multiple rows of comma-separated characters.
N indicates No constraints, or normal.
S indicates that words cannot start with the alphabet in this particular position, but it can be still be used in words starting from other positions.
D indicates that the alphabet in its position is not to be used, that is, Do not use.
Here's a sample constraints file, below.

```
S,N,N,N
N,N,D,N
N,N,N,N
N,D,S,S
```
- Note that the constraints file should have the same number of rows and columns as the input file.
- The constraints file is optional. 

## Solutions file

The solutions file is an optional argument; if used, it should be a file containg words that have already been solved by you. Those words would then not be presented as options.

## Suppressmatches file

A file called supressmatches is also checked and the contents excluded from the permutated word list.

## Usage

- Create the input file, and optionally, the constraints file, for the puzzle you are trying to solve.
- Generate the permuted list
```
python rabbel.py -i inps/20260415 -M6 >apr15.out
[pchengi@viperwolf rabbelrouser]$ wc -l apr15.out
16390 apr15.out
```
- In the above command, we are restricting the generated words to a maximal length of 6 characters.
- Now, execute rabbelrouser.sh with the freshly generated word list as the argument.

```
bash rabbelrouser.sh apr15.out|wc -l
76
```
- If you'd like to only generate 6 letter words, you could do that in this manner:

```bash
python rabbel.py -i inps/20260415 -m6 -M6 >sixletterwordsonly
bash rabbelrouser.sh sixlettersonly
surhet
husera
```
